g.text: Never attended school or only kindergarten
95% confidence interval of impact on weight (expressed as a multiplier)
Compared to a white non-Hispanic woman with Year 12 education, household income $25k-$35k
The effects are complex, but the groups with most education and highest income have the lower weights.
Income and education are related to weight after controlling for sex, height and race
Source: http://freerangestats.info analysis of the US CDC Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System Survey for 2018
